ABUJA – The new Acting Head of the Civil Service of the Federation (HCSF), Dr. Folasade Yemi-Esan, has tasked permanent secretaries, chief executive officers and directors of various Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs) to do away with bureaucracy and embrace innovation in the discharge of their duties in the public sector. Addressing the top echelons of the Federal Civil Service at a onepday Public Service Innovation Conference on Thursday in Abuja, Yemi-Esan charged them to change their “old mindset,” attitude and orientation and embrace innovation and disposition to learn new things to improve the public sector. She further charged them to invest in human capital development and innovative solutions to create value, better performance and improved service delivery. In order to build a robust foundation for innovation in the public service, she revealed that the Office of the Head of the Civil Service of the Federation, through the Project Management Team on Innovation, would establish Service Innovation Department, as well as launch an innovation campaign to raise awareness on innovation through creation of online innovation network.